name: Typhoo Tea administration
summary: Typhoo Tea, the iconic British tea brand, has entered administration after more than a century in operation. The company, which was founded in 1903, has been facing financial difficulties for several years and has now been placed in administration by its parent company, Premier Foods. The administration process could lead to the company being sold, with vape company Supreme reportedly in talks to acquire the brand. Typhoo Tea's collapse is a significant blow to the British tea industry, and it remains to be seen whether the brand will be able to overcome its challenges and continue trading.

Those eligible for these payments, which are intended to support with energy bills during cold weather, include pensioners and low-income households. To find out more about eligibility and payment schedules, consult The Independent and GOV.UK. Additionally, there have been calls for Britons to check their eligibility for a cost of living payment that was activated this week, as reported by Keighley News. Despite the availability of these payments, millions of individuals are missing out, according to Energy Live News. The DWP has issued £25 Cold Weather Payments for eligible individuals, as reported by Cambridgeshire Live, while The Mirror reports that 10,000 people have been identified as eligible for a pay-out.

name: Konate
summary: Liverpool's defensive woes have deepened after Ibrahima Konate and Conor Bradley sustained injuries in the Champions League victory over Real Madrid. Manager Arne Slot has expressed concern about Konate's condition, stating that it is "not a good sign." The club fears the potential loss of both players ahead of crucial fixtures against Manchester City and Crystal Palace. Bradley's timeline for recovery remains uncertain, while Konate's injury status is being closely monitored. Trent Alexander-Arnold's fitness is also a concern after he was substituted in the Madrid game. Liverpool will receive mixed injury news, with hope for Konate's availability and more worrying information regarding Bradley. Konate's injury has caused the defender to shed tears, highlighting the severity of the situation.

name: Jay Slater
summary: In a series of emotional updates, the family of Jay Slater have shared heartbreaking news and revealed how they spent the overwhelming donations raised through GoFundMe. Following the tragic loss of Jay in Tenerife, his heartbroken family halted the fundraiser and expressed their gratitude for the support they received. The funds raised, totaling over £71,000, were utilized for essential costs such as funeral expenses, legal fees, and supporting Jay's young son. The family also shared a final message on the GoFundMe page, thanking all those who had contributed and expressing their commitment to ensuring Jay's legacy lives on.

name: Daniel Khalife
summary: Daniel Khalife, a former British soldier, has been convicted of spying for Iran. Khalife, 23, escaped from Wandsworth Prison in 2021 while being held on suspicion of espionage. His escape involved hiding in a food delivery van. Khalife's mother has claimed that her son is a "James Bond" character who does not live in the real world. Some media outlets have described Khalife as a fantasist, while others have suggested he may have been involved in the world of espionage. Khalife's conviction comes after a trial in which prosecutors presented evidence that he had been in contact with Iranian intelligence officers and had passed on sensitive information.

name: TMJ
summary: Zoe Ball, a British radio and television presenter, has revealed that she suffers from a painful condition known as TMJ disorder. TMJ disorder, or temporomandibular joint disorder, affects the joint that connects the jaw to the skull. It can cause a range of symptoms, including pain in the jaw, headaches, and difficulty chewing. Ball has spoken about her experience with the condition, describing the "awful headaches" it has caused her. TMJ disorder can be caused by several factors, including stress, teeth grinding, and trauma. If you think you may have TMJ disorder, it is essential to see a doctor or dentist for a diagnosis and treatment plan.

name: Frank Lampard
summary: Frank Lampard is poised to make a return to management with Coventry City, the club he represented in his playing career. He is set to replace Mark Robins, who was surprisingly dismissed recently. The Sky Blues are finalizing the terms of Lampard's contract, and an official announcement is expected soon. Lampard's last managerial role was with Everton, where he was sacked in January 2023. This will be his second managerial appointment after Chelsea, where he had a successful two-year spell from 2019 to 2021. Coventry will be his first game in three days.
